Please translate each line literally into English.
124 Come quando, cogliendo biado o loglio, 125 li colombi adunati a la pastura, 126 queti, sanza mostrar l’usato orgoglio,
127 se cosa appare ond’ elli abbian paura, 128 subitamente lasciano star l’esca, 129 perch’ assaliti son da maggior cura;
130 così vid’ io quella masnada fresca 131 lasciar lo canto, e fuggir ver’ la costa, 132 com’ om che va, né sa dove rïesca;
133 né la nostra partita fu men tosta.

query.result:
124 As when, gathering wheat or barley, 125 the doves gathered to the pasture, 126 quiet, without showing their usual pride,
127 if something appears from which they have fear, 128 immediately they leave the bait, 129 because they are assaulted by greater care;
130 thus I saw that fresh band 131 leave the song, and flee towards the slope, 132 like a man who goes, and does not know where he will end up;
133 nor was our company any less quick.
